Natural Language Inference
Compared to the methods from official leaderboard , ReSAN outperforms all the sentence encoding based methods and achieves the best test accuracy .
Furthermore , ReSAN even outperforms the 300D SPINN - PI encoders by 3.1 %. , which is a recursive model and uses the result of an external semantic parsing tree as an extra input .

last best models.from sentence: Specifically , compared to the last best models , i.e. , 600D Gumbel TreeLSTM encoders and 600D Residual stacked encoders , ReSAN uses far fewer parameters with better performance .

recurrent models.from sentence: Compared to the recurrent models ( e.g. , Bi - LSTM and Bi - GRU ) , ReSAN shows better prediction quality and more compelling efficiency due to parallelizable computations .

convolutional models.from sentence: Compared to the convolutional models ( i.e. , Multiwindow CNN and Hierarchical CNN ) , ReSAN significantly outperforms them by 3.1 % and 2.4 % respectively due to the weakness of CNNs in modeling long - range dependencies .
